கொள் denotes  
con tinuation  
certainly  
of the action  
and that the fruit of it reverts to the agent as படித்துக்கொள்ளுகிறான். he continues to study  
குதிரையைவாங்கிக்கொண்டேன். i bought a horse for myself. the verb is generally found in composition with other words as வாங்கிக்கொள்ள  
உட்கொள்ள  
and very rarely in the personal finite forms in common usage  
except in the third meaning. கொள்வாருமில்லைகொடுப்பாருமில்லை there are none who receive  
none who give. கொண்டிருந்துகுலம்பேசுகிறதா? would it be proper to twit a family after you have taken a wife from it?  
